rComments: I took his class at Carleton. He is very knowledgeable and knows his subject really well. He answers the questions clearly and is approachable through emails. He takes the projects seriously but would state his expectations very clearly and gives detailed rubric of the marketing. Exams are easy and are based on overview of the course.

Absolutely not recommend this course. If you have 200% sure that you are a good literature review writer, you may fit for it. Extremely strict professor, gave D for the final literature review. No clues for how to meet his criteria (so subjective), even though he gave the evaluation form. So much content for final exam. Horrible experience.
I learned a lot in his course (Advanced Manufacturing). One of the best profs. I highly recommend the course if you are interested in materials and manufacturing.
